tip.text: Really tasty vegan menu. Try the beetroot and matcha drinks for something a bit different. Everything on the menu is worthy of Instagram.
Really good coffee.
Really good matcha lattes here.

formattedAddress: Realm Park, Burbury Cl. (at Bourke St.)

tip.text: For two, we had the beef empanada, 8hr lamb, mash potato, corn with manchego and flan for dessert. Everything was perfection.
Breakfast plate and fruit salad was good unfortunately the service was not. Wait staff were busy and rushed. Slamming dishes as you clear the table when you're still drinking your coffee is a no-no.
Famous for its very tasty burnt miso ramen. Not far from Nishiki market.

formattedAddress: 中京区十文字町452 (柳馬場通蛸薬師下る)

tip.text: One of the best meals I've had in Tokyo. Long wait in queue though but the food is worth it.
Beautiful ryokan and impeccable service. We were impressed by the kaiseki dinner, the stunning view and the wonderful stories from the owner Tomoko.

formattedAddress: 京都市東山区, 京都府

tip.text: Beautiful park and great for Sakura viewing.
Great market for finding Japanese food like green tea, dried scallops and rice snacks.

contact.facebookName: 上野 アメ横 公式ページ

tip.text: Ok for a burger fix but the taste is pretty average.
Hold in the wall restaurant run by 2 old guys. Come here for tasty and cheap home cooked meals. The beef bowl was delicious and cost only 350 yen.
Soba has great texture. The tempura and egg rolls are popular choices. I had the chicken soup which had a really nice broth. The noodles make the dish. Come before 6pm to avoid the queue.

location.crossStreet: 中出センチュリーパーク 1F

venue.name: Itasoba Kaoriya (板蕎麦 香り家)

tip.text: Great spot to get a view of the city.
Try the crepe cake!

location.crossStreet: 渋谷ヒカリエ ShinQs B2F

venue.name: GIOTTO 渋谷ヒカリエシンクス店

tip.text: Really good burgers!

venue.name: J.S. Burgers Cafe 渋谷パルコ店

tip.text: Go for the novelty but the food is average.
Michelin rated. They cook in front of you - don't touch the grill, leave it to the experts! Rice cake okonomiyaki has a chewy texture.
Get your fruit and seafood fix here.
Not your regular cheesecake. Oozy cheesecake with a flakey base. Yum!

formattedAddress: 心斎橋筋2-3-15 (宗右衛門町通り)

tip.text: Cute donuts that are actually healthier than your normal donuts as they use natural ingredients.

formattedAddress: 西区北堀江1-2-16 (ツリガネビル本館1階102号)
location.crossStreet: ツリガネビル本館1階102号

tip.text: Petite omu-rice is very filling. Comes with fried chicken and pasta salad. Served in a traditional Japanese setting.

venue.name: Hokkyokusei (北極星 心斎橋本店)

tip.text: Great shrine to visit. Come here to see the endless tori gates, fox statues and try the food vendors located at the base of the shrine.

venue.name: Fushimi Inari Taisha (伏見稲荷大社)

tip.text: Try the kitsune udon. The region is famous for its tofu.

formattedAddress: 京都市伏見区, 京都府

tip.text: We stayed in the deluxe room and it is massive for 2 people. 2 double beds, double sinks, large cedar tub and shower. Service is impeccable and the restaurants they recommended were all wonderful!
Tofu kaiseki that's beautifully presented and is a unique taste experience. The tofu is the best I've had with textures ranging from soft and creamy to jelly-like.

formattedAddress: 上大阪町517-3 (木屋町通三条上ル)

venue.name: Tousuiro (豆水楼 木屋町本店)

tip.text: Great location, comfy beds. Rooms are small but it's Tokyo. Wifi was slow. Go for the Japanese breakfast which is really good and skip the buffet breakfast.

venue.name: Shibuya Granbell Hotel (渋谷グランベルホテル)

tip.text: All natural home made ice cream.  Asian flavours like black sticky rice and durian. Try the Yuzu sorbet for something a bit different.
Diner food with an Asian twist. The classic burger was moist with a soft and tasty bun.
The pork buns are great but don't overlook the spinach and shrimp dumplings. These are delicate and packed full of flavour.
The big boy patbingsu is massive and can be shared between 3 people.
Grazing plates are great! We ordered the 3 meats and 3 cheese version and it was enough for lunch for two. Sit by the charcuterie section to watch your plate prepared for you.
Great new speakeasy bar next to Subway. Free shots if you like on Facebook.
Massive servings! Don't let the waiters con you into ordering more dishes. Highlight dish for me was the xo pippies.
Expensive for what you get. Food was ok but was not worth the price.
I ordered the dashi omelette sandwich which was ok but paled in comparison to the pork katsu sandwich my partner ordered. Lucky we went halves. Hands down best katsu sandwich I've ever eaten.
You can't really taste the matcha on the fries but the sauce that goes with it is delicious. Flaming wagyu is good but a bit exy and the sliders were average. Takocini was dry.
Large servings! Mixed plate, fattoush plus drinks for two for under $30. Highlight for me was the baba ganoush on the mixed plate.

If you're familiar with Malaysian food then you'll have heard of nonya cuisine. This nondescript restaurant has authentic dishes like the Ayam Buah Keluak which can't be found anywhere else in Sydney.
Boutique hotel with a rooftop pool which has great views. Staff was friendly but the service could do with more polish. Loved the Malin + Goetz toiletries.
Coffee from sensory lab. Skip everything on the menu and just go straight for the Pancakes.
Get a wagyu set with 4 different cuts for $57. Tteokbokki is on the sweet side which is great if you can't handle your spice.
With Philippa Sibley as head chef, dessert was naturally going to be the best course. Loved the Alice in Wonderland theme for Autumn 2015. Opt for the casarecce over the rabbit for main.
Chargrilled corn and prawn tacos were my highlight dishes. If you're going as a couple after 8pm, you don't have to wait long for a seat.

formattedAddress: 1/11 Collins St (btwn Spring St & Exhibition St)

tip.text: Breakfast with serious flavour - this place does breakfast with flair. Try the yoghurt pannacotta with granola or baked beans with labna and you won't be disappointed.
Visit the Sanctuary. The spa couch and steam room makes it worth the extra $$. The relax massage treatment is also amazing!
Really enjoyed the coffee here - I had The Lost Blend which was full-bodied & robust, the coffee flavour packs a punch whilst maintaining a smooth finish.
Great vibe, super efficient service. Food looks too good to eat and the coffee is spot on.
Don't get the fairy floss..it looks hard to eat! Opt for the cup..it's more practical. Marshmallows are toasted on the spot before serving.
Love this place. Sit on the deck and enjoy the view. Everything on the menu is good! Try the fish and chips or Boathouse salad.
The Nasi Lemak had bold flavours with the curry and sambal giving a punchy spice hit. The roti canai isn't as good as Mamak but the curries here are better.
Pavlova available with chocolate or passionfruit topping. The baby version is a steal at $7.
Same as the Haberfield store. Service is chaotic but if you can stand it, order the ricotta cheesecake and cannoli to reward your patience.
Lamb shoulder is massive. If you're not a big eater, you could share this between 2. Chicken is a winner. Try the loukoumades for dessert.
Hainan chicken rice
